util.
=====

I felt like GNU's coreutils are too bloated, so I'm making my own.
This might also be an implementation for kern. (https://github.com/Tom-on64/kern)

Coding style
------------
Here are some basic things that most of the code should follow.

util.h helpers:
* PROGRAM() macro - define the program name (char* __prog_name)
* AUTHORS() macro - define the author(s) array (char* __authors[])
* OPTIONS() macro - define the programs options (char* __optstring)
* usage() function - print program usage
* version() function - print program version
* error() function - print an error and exit if stat != 0

Usage message syntax:
* Square brackets are optional
* Angle brackets are required
* A ellipsis (...) means more than one argument is possible
* First is the program name
* Then short boolean flags (ie. '[-abc]')
* Next short argument flags (ie. '[-o <file>]')
* After that long flags (ie. '[--color <color>]')
* Lastly unnamed arguments (ie. <file...>)
A full usage message example:
	ls [-adhrt1] [-T <tabsize>] [--color] [--tabsize <tabsize>] [file...]

_NOTE: long flags are currently unsupported :)_

